# Walkthrough - Tavily Enrichment Fix

I have successfully diagnosed and fixed the Tavily enrichment issue. The scraper now correctly enriches jobs with full descriptions using the Tavily API.

## Changes Made

### 1. Fix Missing Dependency
Installed the `tavily-python` library in the virtual environment. This was the root cause of the enrichment being disabled.

### 2. Implementation & Order Verification
- Verified that the enrichment call is made **before** exporting results but **after** deduplication.
- Updated [config.py](file:///Users/apple/Documents/jo%20scraper/indeed-job-scraper/config.py) to reduce `MAX_ENRICHMENT_JOBS` to 50 for initial validation (can be increased back to 200).

### 3. Improved Logging & Error Handling
- Updated [enrich_job()](file:///Users/apple/Documents/jo%20scraper/indeed-job-scraper/tavily_enricher.py#69-114) to use the requested logging format: `logger.warning(f"Tavily failed for {job['link']}: {e}")`.
- Added a startup log in [enrich_jobs_batch()](file:///Users/apple/Documents/jo%20scraper/indeed-job-scraper/tavily_enricher.py#115-149): `"Starting Tavily enrichment. is_enabled={self.is_enabled()}, max_jobs={max_jobs}, total_jobs={len(jobs)}"`.
- Fixed modular logging so logs are prefixed by `[Scraper]`, `[Deduplicator]`, and `[Enricher]` correctly.

